sql:
SELECT observatory_id 
FROM observatory_instruments 
WHERE instrument_id < 1;

SELECT angle
FROM observations
WHERE telescope_id = 1 AND wp05_1 < (SELECT AVG(wp05_1) FROM observations);

SELECT telescope_id, observer_id, wp05_1
FROM observations
WHERE obs_date = '2023-01-01';

SELECT obsr.observer_name, obs.angle * 6371 AS distance_from_earth
FROM observations obs
INNER JOIN observers obsr ON obs.observer_id = obsr.observer_id;

SELECT u.*, al.access_date 
FROM users u 
JOIN access_logs al ON u.user_id = al.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "the most prolific observer" refers to the observer with the highest number of observations;
- "sown the seeds of knowledge" is a metaphorical expression for making observations;
- "garden of observations" represents the collection of all observations.

